  "text": "The association between insulin sensitivity and longevity is still a topic of active investigation. One recent study, for example, found that increasing insulin sensitivity can lead to shorter lifespan in mice, and the mice with reduced insulin sensitivity did not necessarily have shorter lifespan [CITATION_1] . The ITP group has initiated an experiment to see whether the lifespan effect of rapamycin on UM-HET3 mice is altered, in either direction, by administration of metformin.",
